Job Description
The Digital Technology Solutions (DTS) organization at Kimberly-Clark continues to mature the Global Digital Innovation function, with the remit to help ideate, design, realize and scale new digital products and services.

As a hands-on Digital Innovation Portfolio & Program Manager you will have a chance to make a real impact to the business by helping the global EXP Labs team across a variety of key functions, including portfolio and project management (definition, documentation and successful completion of a variety of project activities, ensuring quality, change control and risk management), coordinating cross-functional resources, on-boarding emerging vendors, managing budgets and financial plans, and driving agile ways of working as a SCRUM Master.

This is a critical role with direct impact in the realization of multi-horizon digital innovation opportunities. The right person for this role is proactive with stakeholders, a self-starter who can work under broad direction, and is passionate about delivering world-class, first-of-a-kind project management and scrum master outcomes.
